cs.NA, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the implementation of a Multigrid solver for solving partial differential equations (PDEs) on FPGAs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which deals with the development and analysis of numerical algorithms for solving mathematical problems. The paper also involves hardware implementation, which makes it relevant to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of Handel-C for implementation suggests relevance to cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of performance, which could be relevant to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
